When the user says **Set up project reporting** (or **Apply the project reporting kit**, or **Configure daily Jira Slack reports**):

## Step 1 — Clone + install (terminal first; ask nothing yet)

```bash
cd "$(pwd)"
CACHE="${HOME}/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents"

if [[ ! -f "$CACHE/project-reporting/install/run-project-reporting-setup.sh" ]]; then
  git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE" \
    || git clone --depth 1 git@github.com:codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE"
fi

bash "$CACHE/project-reporting/install/run-project-reporting-setup.sh" "$(pwd)"
```

Then follow `.cursor/skills/project-reporting-kit/SKILL.md` from **Phase 2** (or `$HOME/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents/project-reporting/.cursor/skills/project-reporting-kit/SKILL.md`).

Do not ask the user for a template URL unless clone fails or they provide `PATH:` / `TEMPLATE_ROOT=`.
